%I A397037 #20 Jun 22 2026 21:42:36
%S A397037 0,0,0,1,13,121,1162
%N A397037 Number of transitive relations T on an n-element set such that, for some k with 0 < k < |T|, T has no transitive subset with exactly k ordered pairs.
%F A397037 a(n) = A006905(n) - A397036(n).
%e A397037 For n=3: unique failure is the full relation [3] X [3] (size 9) -- no transitive 8-subset. n=4: 13 failures, all of form A X B with A, B subsets of [4] and |A|, |B| >= 3.
%Y A397037 Cf. A006905, A397036.
%K A397037 nonn,more,hard
%O A397037 0,5
